article.headline: Murray State defeats Northern Iowa 71-43
article.description: — Rob Perry had 17 points in Murray State's 71-43 victory against Northern Iowa on Saturday.
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- — Rob Perry had 17 points in Murray State's 71-43 victory against Northern Iowa on Saturday. Perry had six rebounds for the Racers (9-14, 6-6 Missouri Valley Conference). Jacobi Wood added 14 points while finishing 5 of 6 from the floor, and he also had eight rebounds. Quincy Anderson was 4 of 13 shooting (2 for 7 from 3-point range) to finish with 12 points. The Panthers (12-11, 6-6) were led by Logan Wolf, who recorded nine points. Tytan Anderson added eight points and seven rebounds for Northern Iowa. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
